label.name: Introduction
label.description: Narrative description for set. This is the primary text used when publicly presenting the set.

label.name: Item description
label.description: Narrative description for item in this set. This is the primary text used when publicly presenting the item in the context of this set.

label.name: Presentation type
label.description: Determines how set is rendered when displayed to the public in the Pawtucket/Pawtucket2 front-end.

label.name: Is primary item for set?
label.description: The item marked as primary will be used to represent the set as a whole when included in a list of sets.

label.name: Chronology element code
label.description: Element code of date range element to be used when placing set items into chronological order.

label.name: Authorization date
label.description: The date when the loan was authorized.

label.name: Loan in date
label.description: The date a loan will enter the institution.

label.name: Loan out date
label.description: The date a loan will enter the institution.

label.name: Loan return date
label.description: The date a loan is due back to the lending institution.

label.name: Loan renewal application date
label.description: The date to apply for a renewal to the loan.

label.name: Loan conditions
label.description: A statement of the conditions on a loan.

label.name: Loan note
label.description: General information about the loan.

label.name: Loan purpose
label.description: General information about the purpose of loan.

label.name: Movement method
label.description: The method used in the movement of an object.

label.name: Movement note
label.description: Additional information about the movement of an object or group of objects.

label.name: Planned removal date
label.description: The date an object is to be removed from its current location.

label.name: Removal date
label.description: The date an object was actually removed from its current location.

label.name: Reason for move
label.description: The purpose or reason for the movement of the object or group of objects.

label.name: Introduction
label.description: Narrative description for tour. This is the primary text used when publicly presenting the tour.

label.name: Introduction
label.description: Narrative description for tour stop. This is the primary text used when publicly presenting the stop.

label.name: Georeference
label.description: Location of this stop.

label.name: Description
label.description: An account of the resource.

label.name: Source of description
label.description: Source of item description. This should be a formal citation if possible. For informal sources a narrative description is acceptable.

label.name: Caption
label.description: Short descriptive caption for item.

label.name: Georeference
label.description: Coordinates documenting the location of the item

label.name: Georeference Sources
label.description: A list (concatenated and separated) of maps, gazetteers, or other resources used to georeference the Location, described specifically enough to allow anyone in the future to use the same resources.

label.name: Verbatim Latitude (N/S)
label.description: The verbatim original latitude of the Location. The coordinate ellipsoid, geodeticDatum, or full Spatial Reference System (SRS) for these coordinates should be stored in verbatimSRS and the coordinate system should be stored in verbatimCoordinateSystem.

label.name: Verbatim Longitude (E/W)
label.description: The verbatim original longitude of the Location. The coordinate ellipsoid, geodeticDatum, or full Spatial Reference System (SRS) for these coordinates should be stored in verbatimSRS and the coordinate system should be stored in verbatimCoordinateSystem.

label.name: Georeference Remarks
label.description: Notes or comments about the spatial description determination, explaining assumptions made in addition or opposition to the those formalized in the method referred to in georeferenceProtocol.

label.name: Georeferenced By
label.description: Select the individual responsible for georeferencing this record

label.name: Georeference Verification Status
label.description: A categorical description of the extent to which the georeference has been verified to represent the best possible spatial description.

label.name: GeoNames
label.description: A Geographic lookup that takes search text, passes it to the GeoNames search service and provides a dropdown with search results (ordered by score). Selected geoname is stored as both text (name, country, continent and ID) and the service URL identifier.

label.name: Notes (internal use only)
label.description: Notes regarding item

label.name: Address
label.description: Enter the address detail for the current record.

label.name: Telephone
label.description: Enter telephone contact details

label.name: dcterms:type
label.description: The nature or genre of the resource. For Darwin Core, recommended best practice is to use the name of the class that defines the root of the record.

label.name: dcterms:modified
label.description: The most recent date-time on which the resource was changed. For Darwin Core, recommended best practice is to use an encoding scheme, such as ISO 8601:2004(E).

label.name: dcterms:language
label.description: A language of the resource. Recommended best practice is to use a controlled vocabulary such as RFC4646.

label.name: dcterms:rights
label.description: Information about rights held in and over the resource. Typically, rights information includes a statement about various property rights associated with the resource, including intellectual property rights.

label.name: dcterms:bibliographicCitation
label.description: A bibliographic reference for the resource as a statement indicating how this record should be cited (attributed) when used. Recommended practice is to include sufficient bibliographic detail to identify the resource as unambiguously as possible.

label.name: institutionID
label.description: An identifier for the institution having custody of the object(s) or information referred to in the record.

label.name: institutionCode
label.description: The name (or acronym) in use by the institution having custody of the object(s) or information referred to in the record.

label.name: ownerInstitutionCode
label.description: The name (or acronym) in use by the institution having ownership of the object(s) or information referred to in the record.

label.name: informationWithheld
label.description: Additional information that exists, but that has not been shared in the given record.

label.name: dataGeneralizations
label.description: Actions taken to make the shared data less specific or complete than in its original form. Suggests that alternative data of higher quality may be available on request.

label.name: dynamicProperties
label.description: A list (concatenated and separated) of additional measurements, facts, characteristics, or assertions about the record. Meant to provide a mechanism for structured content such as key-value pairs.

label.name: occurrenceDetails
label.description: A reference (publication, URI) to the most detailed information available about the Occurrence.

label.name: General Note / Remarks
label.description: Comments or notes about the Occurrence.

label.name: Record Number (Collector Number)
label.description: An identifier given to the Occurrence at the time it was recorded. Often serves as a link between field notes and an Occurrence record, such as a specimen collector's number.

label.name: Individual Count
label.description: The number of individuals represented present at the time of the Occurrence.

label.name: Males
label.description: Enter the number of males

label.name: Females
label.description: enter the number of females

label.name: Juveniles
label.description: Enter the number of juveniles

label.name: Sex
label.description: The sex of the biological individual(s) represented in the Occurrence. Recommended best practice is to use a controlled vocabulary.

label.name: Life Stage
label.description: The age class or life stage of the biological individual(s) at the time the Occurrence was recorded. Recommended best practice is to use a controlled vocabulary.

label.name: reproductiveCondition
label.description: The reproductive condition of the biological individual(s) represented in the Occurrence. Recommended best practice is to use a controlled vocabulary.

label.name: Behaviour
label.description: A description of the behaviour shown by the subject at the time the Occurrence was recorded. Recommended best practice is to use a controlled vocabulary.

label.name: establishmentMeans
label.description: The process by which the biological individual(s) represented in the Occurrence became established at the location. Recommended best practice is to use a controlled vocabulary.

label.name: occurrenceStatus
label.description: A statement about the presence or absence of a Taxon at a Location. Recommended best practice is to use a controlled vocabulary.

label.name: Preparations
label.description: A list (concatenated and separated) of preparations and preservation methods for a specimen.

label.name: Preparation Type
label.description: Select the preparation type and any numeric value associated with the preparation

label.name: disposition
label.description: The current state of a specimen with respect to the collection identified in collectionCode or collectionID. Recommended best practice is to use a controlled vocabulary.

label.name: Other Catalogue Numbers
label.description: A list of previous or alternate fully qualified catalog numbers or other human-used identifiers for the same Occurrence, whether in the current or any other data set or collection.

label.name: Associated Sequence
label.description: A list (concatenated and separated) of identifiers (publication, global unique identifier, URI) of genetic sequence information associated with the Occurrence.

label.name: Sequence Identifiers
label.description: Enter the sequence identifier for this particular sequence

label.name: Sequence Identifier
label.description: Enter sequence identifier

label.name: Gene Name
label.description: Please enter the Gene Name for the sequence

label.name: Genbank Identifiers (GI)
label.description: Enter any GenBank identifiers associated with this

label.name: Sampling Protocol
label.description: The name of, reference to, or description of the method or protocol used during an Event.

label.name: Text value
label.description: Enter a text value to refine your sampling protocol

label.name: Sampling Effort
label.description: The amount of effort expended during an Event.

label.name: Event Date
label.description: The date-time or interval during which an Event occurred. For occurrences, this is the date-time when the event was recorded. Not suitable for a time in a geological context. Recommended best practice is to use an encoding scheme, such as ISO 8601:2004(E). See CollectiveAccess Date and Time formats for valid values.

label.name: Event Time
label.description: The time or interval during which an Event occurred. Recommended best practice is to use an encoding scheme, such as ISO 8601:2004(E).

label.name: Habitat
label.description: A category or description of the habitat in which the Event occurred.

label.name: Habitat Text
label.description: Enter the habitat if the dropdown does not apply

label.name: Event Remarks
label.description: Comments or notes about the Event.

label.name: Country
label.description: The name of the country or major administrative unit in which the Location occurs. Recommended best practice is to use a controlled vocabulary such as the Getty Thesaurus of Geographic Names. With its standard country code

label.name: verbatimElevation
label.description: The original description of the elevation (altitude, usually above sea level) of the Location.

label.name: minimumElevationInMeters
label.description: The lower limit of the range of elevation (altitude, usually above sea level), in meters.

label.name: maximumElevationInMeters
label.description: The upper limit of the range of elevation (altitude, usually above sea level), in meters.

label.name: Verbatim Depth
label.description: The original description of the depth below the local surface.

label.name: Minimum Depth
label.description: The lesser depth of a range of depth below the local surface. Enter the unit along with the value. Examples: "1 m", "3 ft"

label.name: Maximum Depth
label.description: The greater depth of a range of depth below the local surface. Enter the measurement unit after the value eg m.

label.name: Minimum Distance Above Surface In Meters
label.description: The lesser distance in a range of distance from a reference surface in the vertical direction, in meters. Use positive values for locations above the surface, negative values for locations below. If depth measures are given, the reference surface is the location given by the depth, otherwise the reference surface is the location given by the elevation.

label.name: Maximum Distance Above Surface In Meters
label.description: The greater distance in a range of distance from a reference surface in the vertical direction, in meters. Use positive values for locations above the surface, negative values for locations below. If depth measures are given, the reference surface is the location given by the depth, otherwise the reference surface is the location given by the elevation.

label.name: locationRemarks
label.description: Comments or notes about the Location.

label.name: pointRadiusSpatialFit
label.description: The ratio of the area of the point-radius (decimalLatitude, decimalLongitude, coordinateUncertaintyInMeters) to the area of the true (original, or most specific) spatial representation of the Location.

label.name: earliestEonOrLowestEonothem
label.description: The full name of the earliest possible geochronologic eon or lowest chrono-stratigraphic eonothem or the informal name (Precambrian) attributable to the stratigraphic horizon from which the cataloged item was collected.

label.name: Date Identified
label.description: The date on which the subject was identified as representing the Taxon. Recommended best practice is to use an encoding scheme, such as ISO 8601:2004(E).

label.name: Identification Remarks
label.description: Comments or notes about the Identification.

label.name: Identification Qualifier
label.description: A brief phrase or a standard term (cf., aff.) to express the determiner's doubts about the Identification. This list is adapted from: Bengtson, Peter (1988). "Open nomenclature" (PDF). Palaeontology 31 (1): 223–227. Archived from the original on 23 January 2011. Retrieved 23 January http://palaeontology.palass-pubs.org/pdf/Vol%2031/Pages%20223-227.pdf2011.

label.name: Type Status
label.description: A list (concatenated and separated) of nomenclatural types (type status, typified scientific name, publication) applied to the subject.

label.name: Type Status Qualifier
label.description: A qualifier for the type status

label.name: Taxon Rank
label.description: The taxonomic rank of the most specific name in the scientificName. Recommended best practice is to use a controlled vocabulary.

label.name: Scientific Name Authorship
label.description: The authorship information for the scientificName formatted according to the conventions of the applicable nomenclaturalCode.

label.name: Name Published in Year
label.description: The four-digit year in which the scientificName was published.

label.name: Identification Verification Status
label.description: A categorical indicator of the extent to which the taxonomic identification has been verified to be correct. Recommended best practice is to use a controlled vocabulary such as that used in HISPID/ABCD.

label.name: Et al
label.description: And others; to complete a list, especially of people, as authors of a published work.

label.name: Distance from Locality
label.description: Distance from locality description. Include the unit with the distance measurement eg 5 mi, 2km, 1m

label.name: Direction
label.description: Cardinal direction of the measurement

label.name: Accession Date
label.description: Date the object was accessioned into the collection

label.name: Date Created
label.description: Date of creation of the resource.

label.name: Measurement or Fact
label.description: The category of information pertaining to measurements, facts, characteristics, or assertions about a resource (instance of data record, such as Occurrence, Taxon, Location, Event).

label.name: Measurement Type
label.description: The nature of the measurement, fact, characteristic, or assertion. Recommended best practice is to use a controlled vocabulary.

label.name: Measurement Value
label.description: The value of the measurement, fact, characteristic, or assertion. Examples: "45", "20", "1", "14.5", "UV-light".

label.name: Measurement Accuracy
label.description: The description of the potential error associated with the Measurement Value. Examples: "0.01", "normal distribution with variation of 2 m".

label.name: Measurement Unit
label.description: The units associated with the measurementValue. Recommended best practice is to use the International System of Units (SI). Examples: "mm", "C", "km", "ha".

label.name: Measurement Determined Date
label.description: The date on which the MeasurementOrFact was made. Recommended best practice is to use an encoding scheme, such as ISO 8601:2004(E).

label.name: Measurement Determined By
label.description: A list (concatenated and separated) of names of people, groups, or organizations who determined the value of the MeasurementOrFact.

label.name: Measurement Remarks
label.description: Comments or notes accompanying the MeasurementOrFact.

label.name: Substrate
label.description: Please enter the substrate

label.name: Parenthetical Authorship
label.description: Whether the authority of the name is to be enclosed in parentheses. (ie when the species has been moved into another genus)

label.name: Category
label.description: DC.Subject - a Dublin Core field that defines the topic of the record. The content for this field is retrieved from a classification scheme modified from one in use at the Australian Museum.';

label.name: Volume

label.name: Pages

label.description: Materials (present in order of sensitivity):

label.name: Conservation Report Condition Rating
label.description: 1. Excellent: Sound, no apparent damage, fully functional, complete (eg. Mint). 2. Good: As for 1, but with obvious signs of wear or tear. 3. Fair/Used: One or two of the following characteristics: Parts missing, obvious wear or some damage, not fully functional. 4. Damaged: All of 3, plus more obvious damage. 5. Poor: Incomplete, non-functional, damaged but able to be conserved.
